</p><div itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/FAQPage">
<div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/=
Question">
<h2 itemprop=3D"name">What is an EAN?</h2>
<div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.=
org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text">
EAN, or EAN13, stands for International Article Number (originally European=
 Article Number). It is an extension of the UPC codes and you'll find them =
as barcodes on most everyday products. Sometimes the barcode is also called=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Trade_Item_Number" rel=3D"=
nofollow" target=3D"_blank">GTIN</a> or GTIN13 (Global Trade Identifier).
</div></div></div>
<p>
</p><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.=
org/Question">
<h2 itemprop=3D"name">Which information is included in an EAN?</h2>
<div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.=
org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text">
The EAN code contains the country of origin, the manufacturer, and a produc=
t number. It also includes includes a checksum for verification.
<p>
When you only look at the barcode, you can't easily see which product it be=
longs to. This website provides an <a href=3D"https://www.ean-search.org/" =
target=3D"_top">EAN lookup</a>, that tells you the product the EAN code bel=
ongs to.
</p></div></div></div>
<p>
</p><div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"mainEntity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.=
org/Question">
<h2 itemprop=3D"name">Is this EAN database complete?</h2>
<div itemscope=3D"" itemprop=3D"acceptedAnswer" itemtype=3D"https://schema.=
org/Answer"><div itemprop=3D"text">
Currently the database includes over 1 billion different EANs. That is huge=
, but still only a subset of all the EANs ever issued.
</div></div></div>

<p>
Page through the EAN database: &nbsp;&nbsp;
